v 0.3:
	client:
	Now using the autotools and supports FreeBSD.
	Use a default configuration file.
	Various cleanings in order to prepare the FreeBSD port and more robust
	code. Better checking of loopback interfaces when searching the local
	IP. Less buggy configuration parser.

v 0.2:
	client: use syslog to log important messages when the client is
	started as a daemon. Add sample configuration files and certificates.
	A few bugfixes, most of them being unlikely to happen. Enhanced
	Makefile.
	rdv server: adjust the behavior of the verbose and debug parameters.

v 0.1:
	First release.
